wwpMacMgmtMIB.name: wwpMacMgmtMIB

revisions.description: This MIB specifies the managed objects for Managing the Mac addresses to the WWP products. This MIB is an extension of the BRIDGE MIB.
As implementation of SAC is different for few of the products, so added the new Sac Table.

wwpMacMgmtMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpMacMgmtMIB.description: Increased maximum value for SAC learn counts.

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpMacMgmtMacTable.name: wwpMacMgmtMacTable
wwpMacMgmtMacTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mac addresses indexed by the Vlan, port and the macaddr.

wwpMacMgmtMacEntry.name: wwpMacMgmtMacEntry
wwpMacMgmtMacEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpMacMgmtMacTable.

wwpMacMgmtVlanID.name: wwpMacMgmtVlanID
wwpMacMgmtVlanID.description: The vlan id associated with wwpMacMgmtMacAddr and the wwpMacMgmtPortId.

wwpMacMgmtPortId.name: wwpMacMgmtPortId
wwpMacMgmtPortId.description: Port ID for the instance. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpMacMgmtMacAddr.name: wwpMacMgmtMacAddr
wwpMacMgmtMacAddr.description: A unicast MAC address which has either been learned by the port or has been statically configured.

wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode.name: wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode
wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode.description: The Mac Addr can be either dynamic or static. For the Static entries the aging time specified by dot1dTpAgingTime does not apply so they stay forever in the Mac Table unless mac table is flushed. Once the wwpMacMgmtStatus is set to 'active', the wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode can't be modified.

wwpMacMgmtMacStatus.name: wwpMacMgmtMacStatus
wwpMacMgmtMacStatus.description: The Mac Address will be disabled or enabled depending upon the protective mode and its Mac Address limit. The added static Mac Address will always be enabled.

wwpMacMgmtMacRowStatus.name: wwpMacMgmtMacRowStatus
wwpMacMgmtMacRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. The RowStatus can't be set to active unless wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode has a valid value.

wwpMacMgmtMacReset.name: wwpMacMgmtMacReset
wwpMacMgmtMacReset.description: To reset the Mac Table for all the ports. A read on this object will always return the 'none'.

wwpMacMgmtPMTable.name: wwpMacMgmtPMTable
wwpMacMgmtPMTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the protected mode attributes.

wwpMacMgmtPMEntry.name: wwpMacMgmtPMEntry
wwpMacMgmtPMEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpMacMgmtPMTable.

wwpMacMgmtPMVlanID.name: wwpMacMgmtPMVlanID
wwpMacMgmtPMVlanID.description: The vlan id associated with wwpMacMgmtMacAddr and the wwpMacMgmtPortId.

wwpMacMgmtPMPortId.name: wwpMacMgmtPMPortId
wwpMacMgmtPMPortId.description: Port ID for the instance. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpMacMgmtPMLearnLimit.name: wwpMacMgmtPMLearnLimit
wwpMacMgmtPMLearnLimit.description: The maximum number of Mac Addresses which will be learned by this Vlan/port pair. This limits applies only for the dynamic addresses.

wwpMacMgmtPMLearnCount.name: wwpMacMgmtPMLearnCount
wwpMacMgmtPMLearnCount.description: The number of Mac Addresses learned by this Vlan/Port pair. If the wwpMacMgmtMacStatus is enabled then the max value for this object should be equal to wwpMacMgmtPMLearnLimit.

wwpMacMgmtPMStatus.name: wwpMacMgmtPMStatus
wwpMacMgmtPMStatus.description: To enable the Protection Mode, wwpMacMgmtPMStatus should be set to enable.

wwpMacMgmtPMMacFlush.name: wwpMacMgmtPMMacFlush
wwpMacMgmtPMMacFlush.description: Setting this object to 'flush' causes all the dynamic MAC entries for the port/vlan specified by wwpMacMgmtPMPortId/wwpMacMgmtPMVlanID to be deleted. An SNMP read on this object returns 'none' once the flush operation is completed.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMac.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMac
wwpMacMgmtCacheMac.description: Specifies whether or not the snmp Agent should cache the Macs in the wwpMacMgmtCacheTable or not. Once a static Mac is added then this object should be set to 'True' again to update the cache.If 'mac reset' or 'mac flush' is used and then the Management Station should set this object to true again to update the Mac Cache Table.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMacTable.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMacTable
wwpMacMgmtCacheMacTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mac addresses indexed by the Vlan, port and the Mac Index.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMacEntry.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMacEntry
wwpMacMgmtCacheMacEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpMacMgmtCacheMacTable.

wwpMacMgmtCVlanID.name: wwpMacMgmtCVlanID
wwpMacMgmtCVlanID.description: The vlan id associated with wwpMacMgmtCMacIndex and the wwpMacMgmtCPortId.

wwpMacMgmtCPortId.name: wwpMacMgmtCPortId
wwpMacMgmtCPortId.description: Port ID for the instance. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpMacMgmtCMacAddr.name: wwpMacMgmtCMacAddr
wwpMacMgmtCMacAddr.description: A unicast MAC address which has either been learned by the port or has been statically configured.

wwpMacMgmtCMacAddrMode.name: wwpMacMgmtCMacAddrMode
wwpMacMgmtCMacAddrMode.description: The Mac Addr can be either dynamic or static. For the Static entries the aging time specified by dot1dTpAgingTime does not apply so they stay forever in the Mac Table unless mac table is flushed. Once the wwpMacMgmtStatus is set to 'active', the wwpMacMgmtMacAddrMode can't be modified.

wwpMacMgmtCMacStatus.name: wwpMacMgmtCMacStatus
wwpMacMgmtCMacStatus.description: The Mac Address will be disabled or enabled depending upon the protective mode and its Mac Address limit. The added static Mac Address will always be enabled.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountTable.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountTable
wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the mac addresses indexed by the Vlan and the port.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountEntry.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountEntry
wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCountEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpMacMgmtCacheMacTable.

wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCount.name: wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCount
wwpMacMgmtCacheMacCount.description: Count of Mac Addresses associated with this Cache Mac Entry. The count will be shown only for the Vlan/port combination which exists on the box.

wwpMacMgmtSacTable.name: wwpMacMgmtSacTable
wwpMacMgmtSacTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the security access control attributes.

wwpMacMgmtSacEntry.name: wwpMacMgmtSacEntry
wwpMacMgmtSacEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpMacMgmtSacTable.

wwpMacMgmtSacVlanID.name: wwpMacMgmtSacVlanID
wwpMacMgmtSacVlanID.description: The VLAN id for this SAC entry.

wwpMacMgmtSacPortId.name: wwpMacMgmtSacPortId
wwpMacMgmtSacPortId.description: Port ID for the instance. Port ID's start at 1, and are consecutive for each additional port. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpMacMgmtSacLearnCount.name: wwpMacMgmtSacLearnCount
wwpMacMgmtSacLearnCount.description: The number of Mac Addresses learned by this Vlan/Port pair. If the wwpMacMgmtMacStatus is enabled then the max value for this object should be equal to wwpMacMgmtSacMaxLearn.

wwpMacMgmtSacMaxLearn.name: wwpMacMgmtSacMaxLearn
wwpMacMgmtSacMaxLearn.description: The maximum number of Mac Addresses which will be learned by this Vlan/port pair. This limits applies only for the dynamic addresses.

wwpMacMgmtSacLearnDisabled.name: wwpMacMgmtSacLearnDisabled
wwpMacMgmtSacLearnDisabled.description: Setting this object to 'true' will cause the learning for the port/vlan pair to be shut off.

wwpMacMgmtSacMacFlush.name: wwpMacMgmtSacMacFlush
wwpMacMgmtSacMacFlush.description: Setting this object to 'flush' causes all the dynamic MAC entries for the port/vlan specified by wwpMacMgmtSacPortId/wwpMacMgmtSacVlanID to be deleted. An SNMP read on this object returns 'none' once the flush operation is completed.

wwpMacMgmtSacStatus.name: wwpMacMgmtSacStatus
wwpMacMgmtSacStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. The SAC entry cab be disabled by setting this object to 'notInService'
